                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.6363/29b.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Ambassador <persName type="to">Herrick</persName>.</hi>
                    <note n="94" xml:id="d1117fn94">Same to the American Embassies at London, Berlin
                        and Madrid, and the American Consul at Tampico, Mr. Bevan.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 29, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Urgent instructions sent yesterday to Department’s representative El Paso, Texas,
                    to endeavor to obtain from Constitutionalist authorities agreement in writing to
                    the neutralization of the great oil producing region between Tampico and the
                    Tuxpam River, and also at Ebano and vicinity to the west of Tampico, in which
                    zone are many Mexican, American, British, and other foreign oil producing
                    operations. The wells cannot be shut in and need most constant and careful
                    attention, and if the oil producing tract becomes exhausted it will be a great
                    national calamity. Urgent representations are being made in Mexico City of a
                    similar nature.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
